The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Metro | The City Diary
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                       The City Diary
                Ajay Raina, the CEO of a call centre in Sector V, was arrested on Friday for slapping a security guard in his office on Thursday. The guard, Malay Acharya, 22, lodged a complaint on Friday morning. Cops have learnt that Raina had assaulted another security guard in his office a fortnight ago.    Residents blocked Budge Budge Trunk Road for an hour on Friday morning demanding the arrest of the real culprits in Wednesdays lynching at Nodakhali. Five men from Birlapur in Budge Budge were mistaken for robbers and beaten up. One died and the others are in hospital. The blockade was lifted after police assured residents that the culprits would be arrested soon.    Twenty-one Bangadeshis are on hunger strike since Thursday morning in Alipore Central jail demanding their early release. They were arrested for illegally entering India six months ago.    Tommy Vianna, a retired teacher of St Xaviers School, died on Friday morning. The funeral mass of the veteran English teacher will be held on Saturday.                                                                                                                                                              
